benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve account audit logs with history by account id

covered: Valid Request: Positive path with an existing accountId returns 200 and a JSON array of AuditLog objects with all required fields
Empty Response: Valid scenario where account has no audit logs returns 200 and an empty array
Authorization: Tests for missing and expired/invalid authentication tokens yield 401 responses
Error Handling: System error scenarios (e.g., database unavailable) yield 500
Boundary/Edge Cases: Tests for invalid/malformed accountId formats, whitespace, uppercase, max length, and partial IDs (TC04, TC14, TC15, TC16, TC17)
Security: SQL injection attempt in path parameter is mitigated and results in 400/404 without exposing sensitive data
Performance/Load: Large audit history retrieval and high-concurrency requests test performance expectations (TC09, TC11)
Regression: Missing mandatory audit log fields are covered by checking all required fields exist (TC12)
Dependency degradation: Degraded dependency scenario covered by TC13
Query Parameter Handling: Unsupported query parameters are ignored (TC08)
gaps: Pagination: No pagination tests for large datasets or page-based retrieval
Authorization: No test for 403 FORBIDDEN due to insufficient permissions
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting/throttling (e.g., 429)
Caching Behavior: No tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or cache behavior
Comprehensive query parameter validation: No tests for valid complex combinations of query parameters (e.g., multiple filters) beyond ignoring unsupported ones
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to verify page size and page tokens across pages
Add tests for 403 FORBIDDEN when a user lacks the necessary permissions
Add rate-limiting tests (429) and throttling under load
Add caching tests validating ETag/Cache-Control headers and caching behavior
Add tests to validate multiple valid query parameter combinations beyond ignoring unsupported ones
Ensure error payloads do not leak sensitive information and have consistent structure across error responses
